task.summary: Default task

Fixed JS Syntax errors that were keeping the page from loading properly.
Put in console.log messages to show which lines loaded properly in the JS.
Added a .properties file.
Adjusted Tomcat folder so that Tomcat will have full control of it.
Set up OJDBC as a global libary.

Cleaned up script.js dramatically. Moving old, but working functionality to JS/Saved Content.js
Added dividing lines. Re-organized JS.
Updated error checking based on whether xhr response was received rather than the ready state since it changes so many times and causes erroneous false errors to be thrown numerous times during the run.

Added debug console messages which include not only what methods are being called but also what variables are being passed into them throughout script.js so that we can better debug and observe the flow. In addition each console.log was tagged with //DEBUG so that finding them would be easier.
Broke login page down to hopefully fix the CSS. Deposited updated Login partial HTML content to the actual partials folder and started the beginnings of forcing it to load if the page ever is empty.

Fixed CSS
Got login page to load on demand from the partial instead of baking it in to the index.html
Deleted newreimb.sql and replaced it with the more comprehensive creation.sql which contains all database entity creation scripts.

Integrated Project Lombok and provided annotations. Removing over 500 lines of code.
Swapped the type of ersUsersID to integer and adjusted every field which references it to call for ints. Did not do this as the AJAX/JSON level as of yet.
Adjusted html to provide HTML5 onclick events since adding event listeners to elements which weren't yet created or on screen yet was proving problematic.

Simplified regex checking to prevent if/else statement from firing in the ERSUserService class. Left pattern matching intact to prevent unnecessary calls to the DAO layer.
Adjusted login() method in script.js to load the dashboard in the event that a JWT is found in window.localstorage after the method finishes executing.
Redesigned ExExpense logo. Got it perfectly centered. Reorganized to use multiple style sheets so that each partial uses a separate stylesheet. All of which are linked in index.html.

Adjusted the front controller servlet switch statement to take both underscores AND dashes so that it will work on both developers devices without changing any configurations.
Added additional logging to the RequestViewHelper to aid with debugging.
Started to add selectors to dashboard.css. Made the text area for reimb_descriptions not resizable.
Started to remove some of the garbage out of dashboard.html

Added in CSS animations to homepage to integrate beautiful slide in effects. Adjusted verifications and login buttons so that they are merely inactive. This will prevent the customer from attempting to contact any other services at all without proper credentials.

Added more advanced field checking to benefit login page. Making it more generic and simultaneously more scalable for use elsewhere.
Added additional activation and animation logic so that the login button will gently pulse when active and become still and inactive when the fields are no longer valid.
Button activation is methodized to work for any element but is primarily meant for buttons.
Still have not done the register fields. Will do next.
Added verification, activation, and deactivation to the register section of the login partial.

Started the beginning of making elements active vs inactive.
When you type in Register it now clears all the fields from Login and vice versa.
Added logs to Account Servlet.
Added JWT Authorization: Principal Key-Value pairs to xhr.headers for the ajaxCall method in script.js
Adjusted xhr.setheader to after xhr.open.

Adjusted JWT logic to check the xhr.responseHeaders. If the response header matches our prefix it will store the resulting header as a jwt in the users local storage.
This jwt is also set to be attached as a header to every outgoing message IF it happens to be in local storage already to allow it to bypass our Java Filter Class.
Cross push to sync with team.
Updated styling and html elements to include an options form for dashboard.view.
Added scrolling pane to the dashboard to house tickets. Begun to implement component based plan to render tickets on screen.
Added Regex to dashboard currency input. Adjusted the color of text elements on the index page so that all will be legible in white.
Adjusted color and positioning on login page.
Adjusted height and position on the page DIV. Still haven't figured out what is causing the page div to be white. Dashboard returns as blue. Started using static px height on the page div.
Removed bootstrap stylings and implementing raw CSS for more manageability.
Revamped login and dashboard pages. Updated javascript. Disabled onload as it wasn't checking accurately for JWTs and was loading the login instead.
Morning push for Justin
Swapped colors on divs for more accurate looking shadows.
Git fix commit
Set a ton of TODOs to give the project more direction.
Saved prettier yet broken login page.
Added a ton of additional logging to better troubleshoot.

Added additional feature to RequestViewHelper to force it to trim down the only the last segment of the URL. This fixed it so that the object should return the appropriate view no matter what computer it is run on. Allowing both of us to successfully troubleshoot.
Added additional HTML to the login page that pulls the variables from the login page automatically and updated the login() method in script.js to allow for you to manually populate a username in password in the event that debugging is ever needed in the future.
Added more logging to every class.
tableJSON method implemented. Need to trim it down or come up with some alternative way of displaying it. Perhaps a 3rd page? Or creative javascript.
